This book will be on earthquakes, a natural disaster that can kill and destroy. But with proper prediction, we can figure out where there is a lot of danger and how to [[Seismic fitness|prevent]] as many casualties as possible. If you are interested in volcanoes, but think that you should learn about seismology as well, then here is the place == Table of Contents == *[[/Plate Tectonics/]] *[[/Basics of Earthquakes/]] *[[/Measuring and Predicting Earthquakes/]] *[[/Seismology and the Seismograph/]] *[[/The Seismologist/]] *[[/Special Topics/]] *[[/Some Earthquakes Around the World/]]
Added IRIS to EQ resources.
== Resources == *[[Volcanoes]]&mdash;Volcanoes and earthquakes are often seen together. *[http://www.usgs.gov/ The US Geological Society (USGS)]&mdash;The USGS researches earthquakes and volcanoes, among other things. *[http://www.earth.dke-guides.com/search.asp?keyword=earthquakes&searchImage.x=0&searchImage.y=0 DK E-guide Earth]&mdash;The DK E-guide to Earth is Internet-linked. Here is the section on earthquakes. *[http://www.iris.edu/hq/ Incorporated Research Institutions for Seismology (IRIS)]&mdash;IRIS is a non-profit consortium dedicated to the acquisition, management, and distribution of seismological data. {{Subjects|Earth sciences}} {{Alphabetical|E}} {{status|0%}}

