== Thursday February 21, 2008 ==

{{User:Whiteknight/HitsTotal|year=2008|month=February|day=Thursday|time=21:00 (EST)|hits=0|threshold=0|books=1|namespace=all}} {{User:Whiteknight/WJHits|total=0}} {{User:Whiteknight/Hits2||0}}

In an approximation termed '''Galilean relativity''', when two objects are moving at <math>\vec{u}</math> and <math>\vec{v}</math> relative to a common inertial reference frame, the relative velocity between the two objects, in the frame of reference where one of them is still, is
<center><math>\vec{v}_{\mathrm{ref}} = \vec{v} - \vec{u}</math></center>

