{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Flagrante| type=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic#Spells|Spell]] (Curse)| features=Causes items touched to become unbearably hot| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Deathly Hallows|''Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows'']]}}
== Overview ==
The '''''Flagrante''''' curse causes an object to become unbearably hot when touched.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
According to [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Griphook|Griphook]], it is apparently fairly common for valuable items in the vaults at Gringotts to be protected with the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Gemino|Gemino]] and Flagrante curses. The latter causes the touched item to become unbearably hot, so that the burglar cannot hold onto his ill-gotten gains.
Despite the similarity in names, this spell has very little in common with the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Flagrate|Flagrate]] spell.
== Analysis ==
